Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Bere","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Beer  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Beer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Erhard, Hans, Heinz, Aloys, Bodo, Erna, Ernst, Frieda, Friedhelm, Hanni.","English (West Country): habitational name from any of the forty or so places in southwestern England called Beer(e) or Bear(e). Most of these derive their names from the West Saxon dative case, <i>beara</i>, of Old English <i>bearu</i> ‘grove, wood’ (the standard Old English dative <i>bearwe</i> being preserved in   Barrow  ). In some cases the surname may be topographic in origin, from <i>atte beare</i> ‘at the grove’. Some may be from Middle English <i>bere</i> ‘woodland swine-pasture’ (Old English <i>bǣr</i>). Compare   Bear   1.","English: variant of   Bear   2 ‘bear’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John de la Bere was born in 1295, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. He died in 1388, in Stretford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 93."},"et":{"1295–1388":"1295–1388","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1312–1394":"1312–1394","1312":"1312","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","Kynardesley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stretford, Herefordshire, England":"Stretford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1295–1388":"1295–1388","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1312–1394":"1312–1394","1312":"1312","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","Kynardesley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stretford, Herefordshire, England":"Stretford, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1295–1388":"1295–1388","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1312–1394":"1312–1394","1312":"1312","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","Kynardesley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stretford, Herefordshire, England":"Stretford, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John de la Bere est né en 1295, à Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il est décédé en 1388, à Stretford, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 93 ans."},"de":{"1295–1388":"1295–1388","1300–Female":"1300–Verstorben","1312–1394":"1312–1394","1312":"1312","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","Kynardesley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Stretford, Herefordshire, England":"Stretford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"John de la Bere wurde 1295 in Herefordshire, 